{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"df725cf6-34eb-4468-846f-03e19ab3557f","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // optional: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why modernize:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`)\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and returns the exception for further assertions\n- It also fails clearly if no exception is thrown","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9e341607-aab2-4aa7-996f-7f74dce18f4b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to explore files.","outputTokens":256,"requestId":"7029:81F2F:BEFA73:DC513A:69F2AF5A"},"id":"2b214de4-48c7-442c-9e9b-49e626387d04","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:24:48.225Z","parentId":"95965471-b939-4f1f-a35f-fd1d7a28d9fc"}
